From Portugal, where de curdel literature originated around the 16th century. and was called “free sheets” (“folhas soltas”), it was brought by the colonialists to the state of Bahia, namely to Salvador, the first capital of Brazil (1549-1960). From there it spread to other northeastern states. At the end of the 18th century. the first national poets of curdela appeared, and literature acquired the status of folk literature [6]. This literature became especially popular at the end of the 19th century. with the advent of the first regional printing houses in Brazil. It was curdel that for a long time served as an instrument of education and information in Brazil.